### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### USERS CRUD OPERATIONS
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### GET all users
GET {{MyWebAPI_HostAddress}}/users
Accept: application/json

###

### GET user by ID (existing user)
GET {{MyWebAPI_HostAddress}}/users/1
Accept: application/json

###

### GET user by ID (non-existent user - should return 404)
GET {{MyWebAPI_HostAddress}}/users/999
Accept: application/json

###

### POST - Create new user
POST {{MyWebAPI_HostAddress}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Alice Wonder",
    "email": "alice@example.com",
    "age": 28
}

###

### POST - Create user with validation error (missing name)
POST {{MyWebAPI_HostAddress}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "invalid@example.com",
    "age": 25
}

###

### POST - Create user with invalid email
POST {{MyWebAPI_HostAddress}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Test User",
    "email": "not-an-email",
    "age": 30
}

###

### POST - Create user with invalid age (out of range)
POST {{MyWebAPI_HostAddress}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "name": "Test User",
    "email": "test@example.com",
    "age": 200
}

###

### PUT - Update existing user
PUT {{MyWebAPI_HostAddress}}/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "id": 1,
    "name": "John Updated",
    "email": "john.updated@example.com",
    "age": 31
}

###

### PUT - Update with ID mismatch (should return 400)
PUT {{MyWebAPI_HostAddress}}/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "id": 999,
    "name": "Wrong ID",
    "email": "wrong@example.com",
    "age": 25
}

###

### DELETE user
DELETE {{MyWebAPI_HostAddress}}/users/3

###

### DELETE non-existent user (should return 404)
DELETE {{MyWebAPI_HostAddress}}/users/999
